  "prompt": "What is the legal framework surrounding money laundering?",
  "response": "The legal framework surrounding money laundering typically involves several key components:\n\n1. International Regulations\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- United Nations conventions\n- Basel Committee guidelines\n\n2. Domestic Legislation\n- Anti-Money Laundering (AML) laws\n- Bank Secrecy Act\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) regulations\n- Suspicious Activity Reporting requirements\n\n3. Key Legal Elements\n- Criminal penalties for money laundering\n- Asset seizure provisions\n- Mandatory reporting for financial institutions\n- Enhanced due diligence procedures\n\n4. Compliance Requirements\n- Transaction monitoring\n- Customer verification processes\n- Risk assessment protocols\n- Reporting suspicious financial activities\n\n5. Enforcement Agencies\n- Financial crime units\n- Law enforcement agencies\n- Financial intelligence units\n- Department of Treasury\n\n6. Penalties\n- Criminal prosecution\n- Substantial financial fines\n- Business license revocation\n- Personal liability for executives\n\n7. Prevention Strategies\n- Background checks\n- Transaction tracking\n- International information sharing\n- Technology-based detection systems\n\nThe framework aims to detect, prevent, and prosecute financial crimes while maintaining financial system integrity.",
